---
@META
dir: src/components/layout
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 7
stack: React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Next.js

@EXPORTS
index.ts: Stack|Grid|Box|Navigation|UnifiedPageLayout — barrel export
navigation.tsx: Navigation — main app navigation bar with auth state & user info
page-layout.tsx: PageLayout — legacy page wrapper with header & content areas
unified-page-layout.tsx: UnifiedPageLayout — new unified page layout with consistent nav & footer
box.tsx: Box — layout container (re-export from ui)
stack.tsx: Stack — flex layout (re-export from ui)
grid.tsx: Grid — grid layout (re-export from ui)

@FUNCTIONS
Navigation() → JSX
  purpose: render top navigation bar with logo, links, user avatar, XP display
  side-effects: none
  called-by: layout.tsx files

UnifiedPageLayout({children,title?,showNav?}) → JSX
  purpose: consistent page shell with navigation, content area, footer
  side-effects: none
  called-by: app page layouts

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: @/components/ui, @/store/user-store, @/lib/constants (ROUTES)
external: next/link, next/navigation, next-auth/react, lucide-react

@STANDARDS
- UnifiedPageLayout is preferred over PageLayout for new pages
- Navigation shows different links for auth/unauth/admin users
- Layout components duplicate ui/ box/stack/grid for convenience import path

@WARNINGS
- page-layout.tsx is legacy — use unified-page-layout.tsx for new pages
- box/stack/grid here are re-exports of ui/ versions — avoid import confusion
